 11  # Pointwise addition, multiplication, and scalar multiplication of sets.
 12  
 13  This file defines `pointwise_mul`: for a type `α` with multiplication,
 14  multiplication is defined on `set α` by taking `s * t` to be the set
 15  of all `x * y` where `x ∈ s` and `y ∈ t`.
 16  
 17  Pointwise multiplication on `set α` where `α` is a semigroup makes
 18  `set α` into a semigroup. If `α` is additionally a (commutative)
 19  monoid, `set α` becomes a (commutative) semiring with union as
 20  addition. These are given by `pointwise_mul_semigroup` and
 21  `pointwise_mul_semiring`.
 22  
 23  Definitions and results are also transported to the additive theory
 24  via `to_additive`.
 25  
 26  For a type `β` with scalar multiplication by another type `α`, this
 27  file defines `pointwise_smul`. Separately it defines `smul_set`, for
 28  scalar multiplication of `set β` by a single term of type `α`.
 29  
 30  ## Implementation notes
 31  
 32  Elsewhere, one should register local instances to use the definitions
 33  in this file.
 34  
 35  -/

 52  @[to_additive]
doc    └─────────┘
 53  def pointwise_mul [has_mul α] : has_mul (set α) :=
 54    ⟨λ s t, {a | ∃ x ∈ s, ∃ y ∈ t, a = x * y}⟩
